-- test/eq_impls.march
-- Test-scoped universal Eq implementation.
--
-- March's typechecker discharges `==` through the `Eq` interface; only
-- Int/Float/String/Bool/Unit/Atom (plus explicit impls) satisfy it.  Depot's
-- tests compare ADTs, lists, options and records with `==` extensively, which
-- is sound at runtime: both the interpreter and the native emitter implement
-- structural equality for data values.  This wildcard impl discharges the
-- typechecker's Eq constraints for the whole test compilation unit without
-- weakening `forge check`/`forge build` for library consumers (it lives under
-- test/, which only `forge test` loads).
--
-- The body is never invoked: the runtime dispatches `==` on the value's
-- concrete type name and falls back to structural equality when no concrete
-- impl is registered (a TVar-typed impl is not keyed under any type name).

mod TestEqImpls do

impl Eq(a) do
  fn eq(x, y) do
    eq(x, y)
  end
end

end
